  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">• We propose a new first-order hyperbolic system approach for dispersive partial differential equations. • We apply a compact 4th-order RD scheme, and solve time dependent dispersive PDEs. • We demonstrate the performance of the high-order RD schemes on the proposed hyperbolic system, including dispersive shock cases. • We verify that the predicted solution, its gradient and Hessian have the same order of accuracy on randomly distributed nodes.</subfield>
